(suspenseful music)

2
00:00:58,558 --> 00:01:01,194
(pensive music)

3
00:02:28,948 --> 00:02:31,618
(bass thuds)

4
00:02:33,186 --> 00:02:35,655
- [Annie Voiceover] This
is the story of a murder.

5
00:02:35,655 --> 00:02:37,257
Several murders, in fact.

6
00:02:37,257 --> 00:02:38,892
(bass thuds)

7
00:02:38,892 --> 00:02:41,361
It begins with the
men in my life,

8
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:43,763
but don't think
it's a love story.

9
00:02:43,763 --> 00:02:45,298
That was my first mistake.

10
00:02:45,298 --> 00:02:47,400
(bass thuds)

11
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,202
In the end it's just
a little fairy tale

12
00:02:49,202 --> 00:02:50,270
about feeling desperate,

13
00:02:51,404 --> 00:02:52,906
and that's what
makes it my story.

14
00:02:54,574 --> 00:02:57,210
I ran away from
home when I was 19.

15
00:02:57,210 --> 00:03:00,446
When I met Bill, he was
the man of my dreams.

16
00:03:01,581 --> 00:03:04,517
Bill used to say it was
love at first sight.

17
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:06,519
Love,

18
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:07,921
(glass crashes)

19
00:03:07,921 --> 00:03:10,790
If that's we started with,

20
00:03:10,790 --> 00:03:12,392
soon faded.

21
00:03:12,392 --> 00:03:13,626
- Annie!

22
00:03:13,626 --> 00:03:14,894
You left this door
open all night.

23
00:03:14,894 --> 00:03:16,529
You know, somebody
coulda gotten in.

24
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:18,798
- Oh, I guess that storm the
other night must've warped it.

25
00:03:18,798 --> 00:03:20,200
- Let's get it fixed, huh?

26
00:03:21,401 --> 00:03:22,902
- I got something to tell you.

27
00:03:22,902 --> 00:03:25,838
- Oh yeah? How 'bout telling
me what's for breakfast?

28
00:03:25,838 --> 00:03:27,340
- Cereal.

29
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:27,974
- Don't they teach you how
to make a real breakfast

30
00:03:27,974 --> 00:03:29,609
in that cooking class?

31
00:03:29,609 --> 00:03:31,010
- [Annie] We haven't gotten
to breakfast yet, Bill.

32
00:03:31,010 --> 00:03:32,912
- I thought you wanted
to learn how to cook.

33
00:03:32,912 --> 00:03:34,981
- This cooking class
was your idea, remember?

34
00:03:34,981 --> 00:03:36,816
- [Bill] So you don't
wanna learn how to cook?

35
00:03:36,816 --> 00:03:37,784
- I didn't say that.

36
00:03:37,784 --> 00:03:39,219
- [Bill] Good.

37
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,687
- I've got something
to tell you.

38
00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:43,223
- 'Cause soggy flakes every
morning ain't cuttin' it.

39
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:44,490
- I got a job!

40
00:03:49,295 --> 00:03:51,998
You know that grocery
store over by the freeway?

41
00:03:51,998 --> 00:03:53,600
Well, I was there the other day

42
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,368
and they were
hiring, so I thought,

43
00:03:56,035 --> 00:03:58,304
why not go for an interview?

44
00:03:58,304 --> 00:03:59,272
- Is that what you thought?

45
00:03:59,272 --> 00:04:01,007
- Anyway, I got the job.

46
00:04:01,007 --> 00:04:02,275
I can start Monday.

47
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:05,712
But I said I'd better check
with my husband first.

48
00:04:05,712 --> 00:04:07,013
(Bill laughs)

49
00:04:07,013 --> 00:04:09,282
- It's, that's, it's great,
honey. I'm proud of you.

50
00:04:09,282 --> 00:04:11,918
Don't think I'm not proud
of you, 'cause I am.

51
00:04:11,918 --> 00:04:13,253
It's just that, you
remember what happened

52
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:15,021
with that secretary
job last year?

53
00:04:15,021 --> 00:04:16,889
All that phoning and faxing

54
00:04:16,889 --> 00:04:19,058
and sitting at the
computer all day?

55
00:04:19,058 --> 00:04:20,994
We never had a chance
to see each other.

56
00:04:20,994 --> 00:04:24,297
Come on, you don't wanna go
through that again, now do you?

57
00:04:24,297 --> 00:04:25,365
- No.

58
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:29,736
- Tell those losers over
at the grocery store,

59
00:04:29,736 --> 00:04:31,437
you know, thanks a lot,

60
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:34,641
but you like it
here just fine, hmm?

61
00:04:34,641 --> 00:04:35,575
Okay?
- Okay.

62
00:04:36,676 --> 00:04:38,878
- (clucks) I gotta go.
I'll call you later.

63
00:04:38,878 --> 00:04:42,048
- [Annie Voiceover] That's
where the trouble begins.

64
00:04:42,048 --> 00:04:43,950
You're isolated.

65
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,318
Alone.

66
00:04:45,318 --> 00:04:46,886
Murder could be the
last thing on your mind.

67
00:04:46,886 --> 00:04:48,621
- 'Cause you married me
and you're stuck with me.

68
00:04:48,621 --> 00:04:52,325
Like the man said, till
death do us part, baby.

69
00:04:52,325 --> 00:04:53,393
(Bill snorts)

70
00:04:53,393 --> 00:04:54,661
- [Annie Voiceover]
But every day

71
00:04:54,661 --> 00:04:56,362
it gets harder and
harder to breath.

72
00:04:57,630 --> 00:05:00,366
(Bill choking)
The more suffocated you feel,

73
00:05:00,366 --> 00:05:01,968
the more you wanna do somethin'.

74
00:05:02,769 --> 00:05:03,636
- I'm okay.

75
00:05:05,705 --> 00:05:07,340
- [Annie Voiceover]
I didn't run away

76
00:05:07,340 --> 00:05:09,042
because sooner or later Bill
would end up killing me.

77
00:05:09,042 --> 00:05:11,411
I ran away because
sooner or later

78
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:12,679
I knew that I'd let him.

79
00:05:14,347 --> 00:05:16,916
That's what it's like
to be a prisoner.

80
00:05:16,916 --> 00:05:19,118
All you can think about
is trying to escape.

81
00:05:19,118 --> 00:05:22,088
You'll rely on
anything. Even luck.

82
00:05:22,922 --> 00:05:25,325
You run for the sake of running.

83
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:27,493
You run even though
there's nowhere to go.

84
00:05:28,861 --> 00:05:30,396
I almost made it, too.

85
00:05:32,532 --> 00:05:35,501
But I always underestimate
how much Bill loves me.

86
00:05:36,602 --> 00:05:38,604
You might say that he
more than loves me.

87
00:05:39,639 --> 00:05:40,540
He needs me.

88
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:43,710
(sniffles) He'll be right out.

89
00:05:44,744 --> 00:05:45,978
- Hey, Annie.
- Oh, Clark.

90
00:05:45,978 --> 00:05:48,147
You scared me to
death. (sniffles)

91
00:05:48,147 --> 00:05:50,116
- I'm sorry. Is Bill ready?

92
00:05:50,917 --> 00:05:52,518
- Yeah, he'll be right down.

93
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,921
- You know, I haven't seen you

94
00:05:54,921 --> 00:05:56,656
since the award
ceremony last month.

95
00:05:58,091 --> 00:06:00,860
- Right. Congratulations,
by the way.

96
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,528
- On what?

97
00:06:02,528 --> 00:06:06,165
- On being a hero, with Bill
and Beth and everything.

98
00:06:06,165 --> 00:06:07,567
- Oh. Yeah.

99
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:09,602
- [Annie] Bill made me
have the picture framed.

100
00:06:09,602 --> 00:06:11,404
You must be really proud.

101
00:06:11,404 --> 00:06:12,905
- I'm just glad nobody got hurt.

102
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:15,375
- Yeah.

103
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:19,746
- You know, I'm gonna
wait by the car.

104
00:06:19,746 --> 00:06:20,913
- Sorry, Clark.

105
00:06:22,181 --> 00:06:25,084
Annie has us running a
little behind this morning.

106
00:06:25,084 --> 00:06:26,719
Okay.

107
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:29,689
Honey, be sure to change
the fluids in the car, okay?

108
00:06:29,689 --> 00:06:30,990
Annie?

109
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:32,625
- I'll take care of it.

110
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:33,893
- How you doin', man?

111
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:36,696
- [Annie Voiceover] So
there I was. Trapped.

112
00:06:37,797 --> 00:06:39,098
No chance of divorce.

113
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,033
No life.

114
00:06:42,168 --> 00:06:43,403
No way out.

115
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:45,805
- This is it?

116
00:06:46,639 --> 00:06:47,673
- What do you mean?

117
00:06:47,673 --> 00:06:48,674
- I mean...

118
00:06:49,475 --> 00:06:51,010
What about a side dish?

119
00:06:51,010 --> 00:06:53,780
How 'bout some sausage or bacon?

120
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:55,982
Since when does
anyone serve eggs

121
00:06:55,982 --> 00:06:58,050
without some sorta side dish?

122
00:06:58,050 --> 00:07:00,586
You know, I gotta be
honest with you, Annie,

123
00:07:00,586 --> 00:07:03,723
it appears as if, by the
looks of this breakfast,

124
00:07:03,723 --> 00:07:04,991
that you're not focusing

125
00:07:04,991 --> 00:07:06,993
on the cooking aspects
of your cooking class.

126
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:12,231
How many men are in that class?

127
00:07:12,231 --> 00:07:15,034
- I've told you a thousand
times, Bill, it's all women.

128
00:07:16,169 --> 00:07:17,103
- You're cheating
on me, aren't you?

129
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:18,070
- I'm not cheating on you.

130
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:20,106
- Just listen to me.

131
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:23,576
You can tell me. You
don't have to lie.

132
00:07:23,576 --> 00:07:24,243
- Bill-

133
00:07:24,243 --> 00:07:25,244
(Annie gasps)

134
00:07:25,244 --> 00:07:26,779
- What? You gonna cry?

135
00:07:26,779 --> 00:07:28,848
You gonna cry like a crybaby?

136
00:07:28,848 --> 00:07:30,550
Just remember
while you're crying

137
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:32,819
who saved you from that
freak called Daddy.

138
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:34,454
If I hadn't come along,

139
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:36,789
you'd still be taking baths
with that sick old fuck!

140
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:37,990
Without me you're nowhere!

141
00:07:37,990 --> 00:07:39,525
- I just want to make you happy.

142
00:07:39,525 --> 00:07:41,027
- Oh, you want to make me happy?

143
00:07:41,027 --> 00:07:42,261
- Yes.

144
00:07:42,261 --> 00:07:43,863
- Then how 'bout a
fuckin' side dish!

145
00:07:45,832 --> 00:07:46,899
- [Annie Voiceover]
Which way do you turn

146
00:07:46,899 --> 00:07:48,167
when there's no way out?

147
00:07:49,268 --> 00:07:50,636
Which way do you turn?

148
00:07:50,636 --> 00:07:52,271
- Ladies?

149
00:07:52,271 --> 00:07:53,239
Gentlemen?

150
00:07:53,239 --> 00:07:54,941
If I could have your attention,

151
00:07:54,941 --> 00:07:56,242
I'd like to introduce you

152
00:07:56,242 --> 00:07:58,478
to the newest
member of our class,

153
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:01,214
Mr. Thomas Nance.

154
00:08:01,214 --> 00:08:02,515
- Ah...

155
00:08:02,515 --> 00:08:04,283
Call me Tommy, please.

156
00:08:04,283 --> 00:08:05,284
- Tommy it is.

157
00:08:05,284 --> 00:08:08,888
(chef chuckles)
- Thank you.

158
00:08:08,888 --> 00:08:10,490
- Hey, Beth.
- Hey, Annie.

159
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,525
How you doin'? Bill said
you'd be here tonight.

160
00:08:12,525 --> 00:08:14,026
Then you realize you're
dying of boredom.

161
00:08:14,026 --> 00:08:15,061
- Eh, it's not so bad.

162
00:08:15,061 --> 00:08:17,296
- (laughs) Yeah, right.

163
00:08:17,296 --> 00:08:18,698
So what are you doin' here?

164
00:08:18,698 --> 00:08:20,500
I told Mike that if
he learned how to cook

165
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,201
I'd be his sex
slave forever, so...

166
00:08:22,201 --> 00:08:24,303
(Annie giggles)

167
00:08:24,303 --> 00:08:26,005
Oh, I get it.

168
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:27,874
Bill gets a little
variety in his menu,

169
00:08:27,874 --> 00:08:29,809
so you get a little
variety in yours.

170
00:08:29,809 --> 00:08:31,043
- No!
- Yes!

171
00:08:31,043 --> 00:08:32,245
I saw you checkin' that guy out.

172
00:08:32,245 --> 00:08:34,247
- No!
- Well, I don't blame you.

173
00:08:34,247 --> 00:08:36,749
I'd kinda like to
peel his potato.

174
00:08:36,749 --> 00:08:38,317
I'm gonna leave you two alone.

175
00:08:42,221 --> 00:08:44,123
- You need a partner?

176
00:08:44,123 --> 00:08:46,025
I could use all the
help I could get.

177
00:08:47,593 --> 00:08:49,128
You know, to be
perfectly honest,

178
00:08:50,296 --> 00:08:52,999
I've always been a miserable
failure at side dishes.

179
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:55,568
How 'bout you?

180
00:08:57,103 --> 00:08:58,004
- Me too.

181
00:08:59,305 --> 00:09:00,573
- I didn't get your name.

182
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:02,275
- Annie.

183
00:09:04,143 --> 00:09:04,176
- That's pretty.

184
00:09:04,176 --> 00:09:07,280
- [Teacher] All right. Now,
tonight we're going to focus-

185
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,581
- Oh.

186
00:09:08,581 --> 00:09:09,282
- [Teacher] On a
plethora of side dishes.

187
00:09:09,282 --> 00:09:11,050
- It's starting.

188
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:12,084
- [Teacher] Okay,
first I want you all

189
00:09:12,084 --> 00:09:13,719
to break into partners.

190
00:09:15,788 --> 00:09:17,123
- Goodnight, Annie.

191
00:09:17,123 --> 00:09:18,357
- Goodnight, Beth.

192
00:09:18,357 --> 00:09:20,226
- [Tommy] May I walk
you to your car?

193
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:23,629
- I don't know.

194
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:26,966
- Who's your friend?

195
00:09:28,634 --> 00:09:31,571
- Beth? Oh, she works
with my husband Bill.

196
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:32,371
- Isn't she a cop?

197
00:09:33,339 --> 00:09:35,174
- How do you know?

198
00:09:35,174 --> 00:09:36,776
- Teacher must've mentioned it.

199
00:09:38,144 --> 00:09:40,046
- [Annie] So you cook?

200
00:09:40,046 --> 00:09:41,681
- A lotta men cook.

201
00:09:41,681 --> 00:09:42,815
- Not the men I know.

202
00:09:42,815 --> 00:09:44,050
- Oh, so you're saying

203
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:46,619
maybe I have an ulterior
motive for being here?

204
00:09:46,619 --> 00:09:47,620
- No! I-
- Like maybe I'm here

205
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:48,821
to pick up girls or something?

206
00:09:48,821 --> 00:09:51,090
- No!
(Tommy laughs)

207
00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:52,992
- It just so happens that
I travel a lot in my work

208
00:09:52,992 --> 00:09:55,661
and after a while
every restaurant starts
to taste the same.

209
00:09:56,762 --> 00:09:58,264
- Where do your
travels take you?

210
00:09:58,264 --> 00:10:01,400
- Oh, Europe, South America.

211
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,902
Last year I went to China.

212
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:03,803
- China?

213
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:06,672
- Would you like to go to China?

214
00:10:06,672 --> 00:10:07,707
- No, I...

215
00:10:07,707 --> 00:10:09,709
Well, I'd kinda
like to go anywhere.

216
00:10:12,044 --> 00:10:12,945
This is mine.

217
00:10:14,246 --> 00:10:15,114
- This is mine.

218
00:10:16,649 --> 00:10:19,018
- So you're not cooking,
what do you do for a living?

219
00:10:19,018 --> 00:10:20,052
- May I take your picture?

220
00:10:20,052 --> 00:10:20,987
- What?

221
00:10:20,987 --> 00:10:22,622
- [Tommy] What's your last name?

222
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:24,423
- Summers.
(shutter clicks)

223
00:10:24,423 --> 00:10:25,691
- [Tommy] Annie Summers.

224
00:10:27,193 --> 00:10:28,027
- How do I look?

225
00:10:28,027 --> 00:10:30,196
(shutter clicks)

226
00:10:30,196 --> 00:10:31,330
- Lonely.

227
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:32,765
(shutter clicks)

228
00:10:32,765 --> 00:10:34,400
- [Annie] Hmm.

229
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,735
- Sorry.

230
00:10:35,735 --> 00:10:38,437
(Annie laughs)

231
00:10:38,437 --> 00:10:39,305
What?

232
00:10:40,339 --> 00:10:41,374
- I just can't
remember the last time

233
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:43,376
a man apologized to me.

234
00:10:43,376 --> 00:10:45,378
- [Tommy] I'll have to
do it more often then.

235
00:10:46,412 --> 00:10:47,647
- You never answered
my question.

236
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:49,415
- [Tommy] What
question was that?

237
00:10:49,415 --> 00:10:51,250
- What is it that you do.

238
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:52,718
- For a living?
- Yes.

239
00:10:52,718 --> 00:10:53,719
- I kill people.

240
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:58,724
(Annie chuckles)

241
00:10:58,724 --> 00:11:00,660
(Tommy laughs)

242
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:01,827
- [Annie] What do you really do?

243
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:04,130
- Ah, photographer.

244
00:11:04,130 --> 00:11:05,798
I'm doing a project on suburbia.

245
00:11:08,401 --> 00:11:11,103
- What would you say if I
asked to take your picture?

246
00:11:12,038 --> 00:11:14,774
(pensive music)

247
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:21,747
- How do I look?

248
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:26,018
- You look lonely too.

249
00:11:29,789 --> 00:11:32,792
(shutter clicks)

250
00:11:34,393 --> 00:11:35,761
- I guess you're
looking pretty forward

251
00:11:35,761 --> 00:11:37,730
to your cooking class tonight.

252
00:11:37,730 --> 00:11:39,732
You got home pretty
late last time.

253
00:11:39,732 --> 00:11:41,967
- I got home around
the usual time.

254
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:43,769
- [Bill] You came home at 10:30.

255
00:11:43,769 --> 00:11:45,271
Usual time's 10 o'clock.

256
00:11:45,271 --> 00:11:46,405
- We must've run late.

257
00:11:46,405 --> 00:11:47,406
- We?

258
00:11:47,406 --> 00:11:48,474
- I must've run late.

259
00:11:50,443 --> 00:11:52,912
- Honey, you don't
get home on time,

260
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,047
I worry about you.

