- Clark?

262
00:12:11,864 --> 00:12:12,765
- Annie, hi.

263
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:16,135
I didn't think Bill ever
let you out of the house.

264
00:12:16,135 --> 00:12:18,771
- Oh, well, I sneak
out once in a while.

265
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,908
Didn't expect to see you here.

266
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:24,143
- Yeah, well...

267
00:12:25,511 --> 00:12:28,781
It's my day off and I figured
I'd better stock my kitchen.

268
00:12:28,781 --> 00:12:30,750
- Well, doesn't Sarah
do your cooking?

269
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:33,753
- Yeah. Yeah, she did.

270
00:12:35,454 --> 00:12:35,487
- Oh, I'm sorry.

271
00:12:35,487 --> 00:12:41,160
- Well, apparently I'm
too boring. (chuckles)

272
00:12:42,561 --> 00:12:45,064
The fact that I'm a lousy
cook didn't help either.

273
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:47,833
- Well, I guess

274
00:12:49,368 --> 00:12:52,471
it's not as easy as we thought
to find the right person.

275
00:12:52,471 --> 00:12:54,774
- Yeah, well, we
all make mistakes.

276
00:12:58,177 --> 00:12:59,812
Listen.

277
00:12:59,812 --> 00:13:01,347
Bill and I go back
to high school

278
00:13:01,347 --> 00:13:04,049
and I know he's not a
prince or anything...

279
00:13:05,785 --> 00:13:07,987
(Clark sighs)

280
00:13:07,987 --> 00:13:11,590
Look, I don't wanna
step on any toes,

281
00:13:11,590 --> 00:13:14,059
but I know people
who could help you.

282
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:19,365
- I called the police
twice last year.

283
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:22,368
I guess when it
comes to protection,

284
00:13:22,368 --> 00:13:23,903
they start with their own.

285
00:13:24,870 --> 00:13:26,172
So I appreciate your concern,

286
00:13:26,172 --> 00:13:27,973
but there's really
nothing you can do.

287
00:13:29,542 --> 00:13:32,444
(ominous music)

288
00:13:32,444 --> 00:13:35,181
(phone ringing)

289
00:13:36,448 --> 00:13:37,616
- Hello?

290
00:13:37,616 --> 00:13:37,649
- Hey, Beth, it's Annie.

291
00:13:37,649 --> 00:13:40,853
Do you know if Bill is
working late tonight?

292
00:13:40,853 --> 00:13:43,222
- Uh, yeah. He was just typing
up a report when I left.

293
00:13:43,222 --> 00:13:44,456
- Oh, I guess I'll
just leave his dinner

294
00:13:44,456 --> 00:13:45,558
in the fridge then.

295
00:13:45,558 --> 00:13:47,259
- Hmm. Look, stop
worrying so much.

296
00:13:47,259 --> 00:13:48,494
And don't be late for class,

297
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:49,562
'cause it's soup
and salad night.

298
00:13:49,562 --> 00:13:51,564
(muffled gunshot cracks)

299
00:13:51,564 --> 00:13:53,199
Yeah.

300
00:13:53,199 --> 00:13:54,466
- [Woman on TV] Why
are we moving so fast?

301
00:13:54,466 --> 00:13:56,635
- Mikey! Honey, can
you turn the TV down?

302
00:13:56,635 --> 00:13:58,571
Mike?
- [TV] Let go of me! Please!

303
00:13:59,538 --> 00:14:00,906
- Come on!
- What are you doing?

304
00:14:00,906 --> 00:14:02,541
(ominous music)

305
00:14:02,541 --> 00:14:04,009
You're hurting me!
(Beth gasps)

306
00:14:04,009 --> 00:14:04,977
Help! Help!

307
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:08,914
(woman on TV screams)

308
00:14:08,914 --> 00:14:11,650
- Now, the first step
in preparing the souffle

309
00:14:11,650 --> 00:14:14,253
is a very challenging one.

310
00:14:14,253 --> 00:14:16,622
Again, crack your egg
on the side of the bowl.

311
00:14:17,656 --> 00:14:18,924
Good.

312
00:14:18,924 --> 00:14:21,026
Now tip the egg to one side

313
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:24,196
and carefully pass the yolk

314
00:14:24,196 --> 00:14:26,932
from one half of the
shell into the other.

315
00:14:26,932 --> 00:14:28,667
And there, you see?

316
00:14:29,935 --> 00:14:30,669
It's easy.

317
00:14:31,904 --> 00:14:31,937
- (laughs) You did it.

318
00:14:31,937 --> 00:14:35,174
- Not without making
a mess in the process.

319
00:14:41,614 --> 00:14:42,648
Sorry.

320
00:14:42,648 --> 00:14:43,916
If I lost this,

321
00:14:45,517 --> 00:14:47,653
you never would've forgiven me.

322
00:14:47,653 --> 00:14:50,322
(soft music)

323
00:14:53,025 --> 00:14:56,495
- [Teacher] Has anyone
seen Beth tonight?

324
00:14:57,329 --> 00:14:58,230
You sure?

325
00:15:05,037 --> 00:15:06,305
- [Annie] Where were we?

326
00:15:06,305 --> 00:15:07,239
- My parents.

327
00:15:08,641 --> 00:15:12,177
Pretty much raised myself. I
did some time in the military.

328
00:15:12,177 --> 00:15:13,479
That's where I started
to get interested

329
00:15:13,479 --> 00:15:14,680
in photographing things.

330
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:15,581
What about you?

331
00:15:17,182 --> 00:15:20,686
- Oh, my mom died when I was 12

332
00:15:20,686 --> 00:15:24,590
and my dad, well, I think
he's alive somewhere.

333
00:15:25,724 --> 00:15:27,993
We didn't really get
along, so I ran away.

334
00:15:29,161 --> 00:15:30,496
That's when I met Bill.

335
00:15:30,496 --> 00:15:33,098
- Coffee and one peach pie.

336
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:34,500
- Thank you.
- Anything else?

337
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:35,935
- No.
- Okay.

338
00:15:35,935 --> 00:15:37,002
If you need anything
else, just gimme a holler.

339
00:15:37,002 --> 00:15:38,070
- Thanks.

340
00:15:40,472 --> 00:15:42,408
May I ask you something?

341
00:15:42,408 --> 00:15:44,376
- Sure.
- What would your husband do

342
00:15:44,376 --> 00:15:45,978
if you lost your wedding ring?

343
00:15:49,048 --> 00:15:50,015
Would he hurt you?

344
00:15:53,218 --> 00:15:54,453
Ah...

345
00:15:54,453 --> 00:15:56,455
Look, I'm sorry. It's
none of my business.

346
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:58,757
- No, and it's, um,

347
00:15:59,525 --> 00:16:00,759
it's not your problem.

348
00:16:00,759 --> 00:16:01,994
I, uh...

349
00:16:04,196 --> 00:16:05,130
I really,

350
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:06,065
I really should get going.

351
00:16:06,065 --> 00:16:08,000
- If somebody's hurting you,

352
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,201
they should be stopped.

353
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:14,139
(somber music)

354
00:16:15,007 --> 00:16:16,241
- Sometimes he hits me.

355
00:16:17,276 --> 00:16:18,344
- [Tommy] Sometimes?

356
00:16:20,679 --> 00:16:22,247
- A lot.

357
00:16:22,247 --> 00:16:23,749
- Have you gone to the police?

358
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:27,987
- [Annie] Twice. But
they can't do anything.

359
00:16:32,624 --> 00:16:35,494
- Well, maybe I could
offer another alternative.

360
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:39,064
I knew a woman

361
00:16:40,199 --> 00:16:41,800
who went through the same things

362
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,736
you're going through
with her husband.

363
00:16:47,039 --> 00:16:48,007
- What did she do?

364
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:51,043
- [Tommy] She had him killed.

365
00:16:53,746 --> 00:16:55,014
- How?

366
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,548
- You don't wanna know.

367
00:16:56,548 --> 00:16:57,750
- [Annie] I do.

368
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:57,783
- Pretty terrible.

369
00:17:01,153 --> 00:17:03,555
She had him decapitated
with an axe.

370
00:17:04,623 --> 00:17:06,825
- Oh my god.
- While he was sleeping.

371
00:17:08,627 --> 00:17:09,595
- That's so

372
00:17:10,662 --> 00:17:11,563
Perfect.

373
00:17:13,065 --> 00:17:14,666
- See, I'm glad
you feel that way.

374
00:17:15,634 --> 00:17:17,436
I told her... (laughs)

375
00:17:17,436 --> 00:17:20,439
I said, don't do it like
that. It's so messy.

376
00:17:20,439 --> 00:17:24,076
You see, my motto is
keep things simple.

377
00:17:24,076 --> 00:17:25,844
Do your homework, carefully.

378
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:31,417
The rest is, ah,
execution, so to speak.

379
00:17:31,417 --> 00:17:34,253
(brooding music)

380
00:17:34,253 --> 00:17:35,788
- What happened to the woman?

381
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:37,790
- I don't know.

382
00:17:40,325 --> 00:17:43,128
I'd like to think that she
lived happily ever after.

383
00:17:47,332 --> 00:17:49,435
- [Annie] So where do you
stay while you're in town?

384
00:17:49,435 --> 00:17:51,070
- Oh, I have this place downtown

385
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:52,104
I like to stay at
whenever I'm here.

386
00:17:52,104 --> 00:17:53,772
- Uh-huh. Hotel?

387
00:17:53,772 --> 00:17:55,074
- No, that's too public.

388
00:17:56,775 --> 00:17:58,110
I do business here more and more

389
00:17:58,110 --> 00:17:59,411
so I finally rented a place.

390
00:18:00,345 --> 00:18:01,280
It's really nice.

391
00:18:02,614 --> 00:18:05,451
You oughta come visit sometime.
Do you ever get downtown?

392
00:18:05,451 --> 00:18:07,853
- No, you know. My husband.

393
00:18:08,854 --> 00:18:10,089
- Ah.

394
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:14,660
You know, in China they have
this saying about women:

395
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:17,096
"She can live the
life of a prisoner,

396
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:19,231
she can live the
life of a princess,

397
00:18:20,199 --> 00:18:21,600
or she could be herself."

398
00:18:22,434 --> 00:18:25,170
(pensive music)

399
00:18:33,679 --> 00:18:34,646
Which one are you?

400
00:18:37,382 --> 00:18:38,617
- Oh, this is getting confusing.

401
00:18:38,617 --> 00:18:40,586
- No. This is getting exciting.

402
00:18:43,722 --> 00:18:46,792
(crickets chirping)

403
00:19:00,172 --> 00:19:02,141
- [Bill] You coulda called.

404
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:03,709
I was getting ideas.

405
00:19:05,177 --> 00:19:06,645
- I...

406
00:19:06,645 --> 00:19:06,678
I'm sorry.

407
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:10,949
I stayed late to help clean up.

408
00:19:10,949 --> 00:19:14,620
- (laughs) I don't want you
going to that class anymore.

409
00:19:16,722 --> 00:19:17,623
- Bill.

410
00:19:19,291 --> 00:19:23,162
- I know I didn't turn out
the way you wanted me to.

411
00:19:23,162 --> 00:19:25,197
And I know I'm not perfect.

412
00:19:25,197 --> 00:19:27,599
(cylinder clicking)

413
00:19:27,599 --> 00:19:30,235
But you don't have
to go cheat on me.

414
00:19:30,235 --> 00:19:31,537
- I'm not.

415
00:19:31,537 --> 00:19:32,571
- Don't lie to me.

416
00:19:32,571 --> 00:19:34,173
- Bill!

417
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:36,341
Just give it to me.

418
00:19:36,341 --> 00:19:39,244
(ominous music)

419
00:19:41,747 --> 00:19:43,415
Take it.

420
00:19:43,415 --> 00:19:45,384
Before I do something
stupid with it.

421
00:19:45,384 --> 00:19:47,352
(Annie gasps)

422
00:19:47,352 --> 00:19:48,453
- No, Bill! Bill!

423
00:19:48,453 --> 00:19:49,888
- Who is it?
- No! No one, please!

424
00:19:49,888 --> 00:19:50,923
- Who is it?
- No one!

425
00:19:50,923 --> 00:19:51,924
- You're killing me!

426
00:19:51,924 --> 00:19:53,892
(Annie screams)
(hammer clicks)

427
00:19:53,892 --> 00:19:56,295
(Bill sobs)

428
00:20:01,934 --> 00:20:04,670
Just don't go to
that class anymore.

429
00:20:04,670 --> 00:20:08,307
I don't want you going
to that class, okay?

430
00:20:09,408 --> 00:20:11,710
- Murder-suicide. It's
the third one this year.

431
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:13,245
Excuse me.

432
00:20:13,245 --> 00:20:15,647
Husband takes her out, then
he sits in his favorite chair

433
00:20:15,647 --> 00:20:17,316
and turns the gun on himself.

434
00:20:17,983 --> 00:20:19,218
Did you know him?

435
00:20:19,985 --> 00:20:21,853
- No, not enough
to explain this.

436
00:20:22,955 --> 00:20:25,290
- It's tough. I
gotta take a piss.

437
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:26,592
You wanna finish this?

438
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:28,694
- No thanks.

439
00:20:28,694 --> 00:20:31,997
(police radio chatter)

440
00:20:35,968 --> 00:20:37,269
(bell chimes)

441
00:20:37,269 --> 00:20:39,037
- [Waitress] Here you go.

442
00:20:42,507 --> 00:20:43,775
- Thanks for meeting me.

443
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:46,812
- You all right?
- Yeah, I am.

444
00:20:46,812 --> 00:20:49,615
I had to wait for Bill
to leave for work.

445
00:20:49,615 --> 00:20:51,650
- [Tommy] Well, you sounded
so upset on the phone.

446
00:20:51,650 --> 00:20:53,051
- Yeah, well, uh...

447
00:20:54,586 --> 00:20:56,288
I can't come to class anymore.

448
00:20:57,389 --> 00:20:59,625
I wanted to say goodbye
to you face to face.

449
00:21:00,692 --> 00:21:02,527
I didn't want you to
think I was mad at you.

450
00:21:05,497 --> 00:21:06,665
- You could leave him.

451
00:21:07,966 --> 00:21:08,900
- He'd find me.

452
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:10,902
- [Tommy] You could run away.

453
00:21:10,902 --> 00:21:11,837
- I've got nowhere to go.

454
00:21:11,837 --> 00:21:13,038
- You could come with me.

455
00:21:15,707 --> 00:21:16,575
Annie.

456
00:21:17,843 --> 00:21:19,511
Come away with me.

457
00:21:22,748 --> 00:21:24,883
- I don't even know you.

458
00:21:24,883 --> 00:21:25,951
- You know enough.

459
00:21:28,053 --> 00:21:29,588
I'll be leaving soon.

460
00:21:32,457 --> 00:21:34,593
I want you to go with me.

461
00:21:35,761 --> 00:21:37,529
I want to take care of you.

462
00:21:37,529 --> 00:21:39,431
It's simpler than
you think, Annie.

463
00:21:40,866 --> 00:21:42,634
One day you wake up,

464
00:21:43,602 --> 00:21:44,703
you're someplace new,

465
00:21:45,671 --> 00:21:46,805
someplace beautiful.

466
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:49,308
No Bill.

467
00:21:50,509 --> 00:21:51,576
Just you and me.

468
00:21:52,878 --> 00:21:55,681
(brooding music)

469
00:21:59,851 --> 00:22:00,686
- I can't.

470
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:03,055
- I can.

471
00:22:08,093 --> 00:22:09,328
- I can't.

472
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:13,899
I can't.

473
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:16,368
Goodbye.

474
00:22:17,703 --> 00:22:20,439
(ominous music)

475
00:22:24,743 --> 00:22:27,412
(Zippo clinks)

476
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:43,362
(floorboard creaks)

477
00:22:47,799 --> 00:22:48,700
Bill?

478
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:56,174
Bill?

479
00:23:00,078 --> 00:23:00,912
Bill?

480
00:23:04,049 --> 00:23:05,016
You're home early.

481
00:23:06,418 --> 00:23:07,452
- Daddy was right.

482
00:23:11,890 --> 00:23:13,992
Give the bitch an inch

483
00:23:13,992 --> 00:23:15,861
and she'll rip your
fuckin' arm off.

484
00:23:16,695 --> 00:23:17,596
- What's wrong?

485
00:23:20,132 --> 00:23:21,700
- I had a bad day today.

486
00:23:24,636 --> 00:23:25,537
Beth's dead.

487
00:23:29,007 --> 00:23:29,908
- What?

488
00:23:31,009 --> 00:23:33,412
- [Bill] Mike killed her.

489
00:23:33,412 --> 00:23:34,146
- What?

490
00:23:35,147 --> 00:23:37,549
- I came home to tell you,

491
00:23:38,450 --> 00:23:39,684
but you weren't here.

492
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:43,455
So I went looking for you.

493
00:23:44,689 --> 00:23:47,426
(ominous music)

494
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,231
Get off my fuckin' bed.

495
00:23:55,434 --> 00:23:57,769
(belt buckle rattles)

496
00:23:57,769 --> 00:23:58,937
- Bill, no!

497
00:23:58,937 --> 00:23:59,771
No!

498
00:23:59,771 --> 00:24:01,039
- [Bill] Let go of that!

499
00:24:01,039 --> 00:24:02,507
Let it go! Who is he?
- No, Bill! Please!

500
00:24:02,507 --> 00:24:03,875
- Who, you bitch?

501
00:24:03,875 --> 00:24:04,843
Fucking bitch!

502
00:24:04,843 --> 00:24:06,211
- [Annie] No! Stop it, Bill!

503
00:24:06,211 --> 00:24:08,046
No! (screams)

504
00:24:08,046 --> 00:24:09,114
- Who is it?

505
00:24:10,081 --> 00:24:11,216
Who is it?

506
00:24:11,216 --> 00:24:12,517
- [Annie] No! No!

507
00:24:12,517 --> 00:24:13,985
Please!

508
00:24:13,985 --> 00:24:16,855
(thunder rumbles)

509
00:24:16,855 --> 00:24:19,524
- [Clark] Hey, you
got my messages?

510
00:24:19,524 --> 00:24:20,459
- You forgot your faxes again.

511
00:24:20,459 --> 00:24:21,726
- Hey, I'm sorry.

512
00:24:21,726 --> 00:24:24,496
- Try checking your
box once in a while?

513
00:24:24,496 --> 00:24:27,232
(ominous music)

514
00:24:32,103 --> 00:24:34,473
(man whistles)

515
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:37,542
(mouths silently)

516
00:24:43,782 --> 00:24:44,683
- Damn.

517
00:24:58,296 --> 00:24:59,531
Annie?

518
00:25:00,665 --> 00:25:01,566
Annie?

519
00:25:02,901 --> 00:25:03,969
- Hi, Clark.

520
00:25:04,769 --> 00:25:05,837
- Oh my god.

521
00:25:06,738 --> 00:25:08,240
- [Annie] It's gonna be okay.

522
00:25:11,309 --> 00:25:12,744
- I want you to take this.

523
00:25:17,249 --> 00:25:19,818
And you use it if you need me.

524
00:25:22,954 --> 00:25:23,855
Take it.

525
00:25:26,625 --> 00:25:27,993
(Annie moans softly)

526
00:25:27,993 --> 00:25:30,795
(brooding music)

527
00:25:35,567 --> 00:25:40,639
(distant bell tolls)
(thunder rumbles)

528
00:25:46,578 --> 00:25:49,214
(rain pattering)

529
00:25:50,348 --> 00:25:52,083
- You won't have to do anything.

530
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:55,053
- There's nothing you can do.

531
00:25:56,054 --> 00:25:57,289
- I know.

532
00:25:57,289 --> 00:25:58,356
